data.name: Maple Glazed Apple Cider Donuts
data.quickTastyDescription: Delightfully sweet and spiced, these baked donuts are infused with apple cider and topped with a rich maple glaze.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C) and grease a donut pan.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt.
In another bowl, whisk together the eggs, apple cider, and melted butter until well combined.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined.
Spoon the batter into the prepared donut pan, filling each cavity about 3/4 full.
Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into a donut comes out clean.
Allow the donuts to cool in the pan for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.
For the maple glaze, whisk together the maple syrup and powdered sugar until smooth.
Dip the cooled donuts in the glaze and allow the excess to drip off before serving.
